## Limitations

This report is based on data and articles available up to October 2023. The rapidly evolving nature of the pandemic and its political implications means that new developments may not be covered. Additionally, the reliance on secondary sources may introduce bias based on the perspectives of the original authors. Further research and real-time data analysis are recommended for a more comprehensive understanding of the ongoing impact of COVID-19 on global freedoms.